column4: "There will never be another you"
"dougmck@pipeline.com.au - markers are comments on things that might be of interest especially to piano players.\012"
"Played in real time - demonstrates development of melodic or rhythmic motifs\012"
"Play each melody note twice"
"Staccato 'Stabs' with LH are just ahead of beats 1 and 3 - and anticipate each new chord"
"More melody notes played twice "
"Red Garland type of voicing -LH plays standard rootless voicing - RH plays Octaves with (usually) perfect 5th"
"Notes in pairs - descend down appropriate scale"
"Figure based on G triad target tones linked with chromatic coonecting tones"
"Dim scale on Bb7 - continues across barlines before resolving"
"On Eb7 chord - Dim scale in 16th notes"
"A rhythmic idea - chord tones and lower diatonic neighbour - same rhythm continues up then back down"
"Phrase increases in Volume and thickness of voicing"
"A little melodic phrase on EbMaj7"
"Same idea carried into new position with Dm7b5-G7alt chord"
"Idea continues  over Cm"
"5th(Bb) and upper neighbour"
"Surround the 3rd (G)"
"Pairs of notes made into a rhythm and carried down"
"Art Tatum type run - G/F - G triad has Black notes under each triad note - so this is easy to execute"
"More 'Red Garland' type voicings"
"Usinf George Shearing type block harmony - RH plays chord under melody and LH doubles melody below"
"Back to theme"
